Stopped out today to get some info for your new liner. All-in-all, the liner can be replaced and I don t think we will have much trouble doing so, however, your equipment does need some attention. The electrical box will need to be tested and possibly upgraded by an electrician. The pump may also need to be replaced. It is recommended to replace the sand in the filter every 5-7 years, so I would recommend that as well. It did not appear that the skimmers were winterized, but we will not know of any possible underground leaks until after the system is running. With that said, if you are interested, we would be looking at the 2nd to 3rd week of June for getting your project completed. If you have any questions or would like to provide the deposit for the installation, please let us know! Thank you
